=comment Package: Gtk4, C-Source: alertdialog
use v6.d;

#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#--[Class Description]----------------------------------------------------------
#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

=begin pod
=TITLE Gnome::Gtk4::AlertDialog
=head1 Description

Collects the arguments that are needed to present a message to the user.

The message is shown with the L<.choose()|#choose> function.

If you don't need to wait for a button to be clicked, you can use L<.show()|#show>.

=head2 Uml Diagram
=for image :src<asset_files/images/plantuml/AlertDialog.png> :width<70%> :class<inline>

=begin comment

=head2 Example
# Example use of module Gnome::Gtk4::AlertDialog

=end comment

=end pod

