#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
=begin pod
=head2 show

Shows the alert to the user.

This function is a simpler version of L<.choose()|#choose> intended for dialogs with a single button.

If you want to cancel the dialog or if the alert has more than one button, you should use that function instead and provide it with a B<Gnome::Gtk4::AlertDialog> and callback respectively.

=begin code
method show ( N-Object() $parent )
=end code

=item $parent; the parent window.

=begin comment

=head2 Example
# Example for show

=end comment

=end pod

